\ qnorm ( p -- z ), the standard normal quantile (inverse CDF): Acklam's
\ rational approximation, three regions split at 0.02425 and 0.97575;
\ errors unless p is strictly inside (0, 1).

\ === central region ===
0.5 qnorm . cr                \ 0
0.3 qnorm . cr                \ -0.524401
0.7 qnorm . cr                \ 0.524401
0.025 qnorm . cr              \ -1.95996
0.975 qnorm . cr              \ 1.95996

clear

\ === tails (outside the 0.02425 / 0.97575 region breaks) ===
0.01 qnorm . cr               \ -2.32635
0.99 qnorm . cr               \ 2.32635
0.001 qnorm . cr              \ -3.09023
0.999 qnorm . cr              \ 3.09023
1e-10 qnorm . cr              \ -6.36134

clear

\ === symmetry: qnorm(p) = -qnorm(1-p) ===
0.42 qnorm 0.58 qnorm + abs 1e-12 < . cr    \ 1 (central)
0.02 qnorm 0.98 qnorm + abs 1e-12 < . cr    \ 1 (tails)

clear

\ === errors (thrown; caught here to show the message) ===
[: 0 qnorm :] [: . cr :] try-catch           \ (p = 0)
[: 1 qnorm :] [: . cr :] try-catch           \ (p = 1)
[: -0.5 qnorm :] [: . cr :] try-catch        \ (negative)
[: 2 qnorm :] [: . cr :] try-catch           \ (above 1)
